    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="454"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296A1/66: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                            type="from">Garrett</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-20T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 20, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 20—2:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Today the British Government suggested to the Italian Government that they
                    represent to Germany the dangers of failure of the <pb facs="0773" n="653"
                        xml:id="pg_653"/> Lausanne Conference and suggest that a preliminary
                    agreement be reached to extend the <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Hoover</persName>
                    moratorium for so long as may be necessary to prepare the way for a conference
                    that may be looked forward to with some measure of hope of success but for a
                    maximum of 9 months. <persName corresp="#p_GD1">Grandi</persName> tells me he
                    thinks that the British Government had consulted France before making this
                    suggestion but so far as he knows France has not yet agreed to it. Nevertheless,
                        <persName corresp="#p_GD1">Grandi</persName> sent instructions to Berlin
                    this afternoon in the sense indicated.</p>
                <p>Cipher text mailed to Paris, London, Berlin, Brussels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
